    "Specifically, if we let y(X, E, g) be the label given to the graph featurised with X, E, g, then for every transformation g 2 G, the following property holds: yðgðXÞ, gðEÞ, gðgÞÞ = yðX, E, gÞ ð 5Þ",
    "This condition is also referred to as G-invariance.",
    "Here, by gðXÞ we denote the result of transforming X by g-a concept also known as a group action.",
    "More generally, it is a function of the form G × S!",
    "S for some state set S. Note that a single group element, g 2 G can easily produce different actions on different S-in this case, S could be R jVj × k (X), R jVj × jVj × l (E) and R m (g)."
